ics and semantically grounded priors. To prevent over-reliance on potentially noisy LLM outputs, we introduce a confidence-gated fusion mechanism that dynamically weights LLM-informed vs. data-derived prototype components based on uncertainty estimates. This ensures robustness while enhancing generalization in open-world settings. Furthermore, we extend the contrastive adversarial loss to include *semantic consistency*, ensuring generated embeddings align not only with their prototype distribution but also with the underlying LLM-encoded class semantics. This bridges the gap between perceptual similarity and conceptual coherence—a missing piece in current few-shot GANs.

